Napoli kept their Italian Serie A title run with a 2-1 away victory against Lecce on Friday. Former Fenerbahce defender Min-jae Kim assisted Italian defender Giovanni Di Lorenzo’s goal in minute 18, giving Napoli the lead at Stadio Via del Mare in Lecce. Lecce winger Federico Di Francesco leveled the score in the 52nd minute. The home team’s defender Antonio Gallo’s own goal in minute 64, turned out to be the winning goal for the Blues, with the game ending 2-1. Napoli, who have 73 points, kept their run with a 19-point gap between them and runners-up Lazio in the Serie A standings. (SOURCE: Anadolu Agency)